The society is getting older and this is a huge problem for many developed countries. Elderly people are retired and younger generations must pay for their pensions. Also, retirees are not able to do many of everyday activities, such as doing groceries, because of their health.
On island Wight government has begun volunteering program to deal with that problem. Volunteers are helping elderly people. Every hour of work equals one hour of help for you, when you will retire. I think it is a good idea, although it may not work.
People can help each other with some easy activities. If retirees have received free help it would decrease country's financial expenses. Also, volunteers know that they would get help too, when they will be older. But there is one problem.
Not many young people think of their retirement. Youth is concerned about the present, not the future. It may cause lack of interest in volunteering.
Also, there is a risk that government will give up on this program untill volunteers get retire. Some people don't want to help others unless they receive something for that.
In summary, I think the idea is good, but it is possible that there wiil be no volunteers.
